Antagony's pod was done now, and it opened and let her out. She stood up and 
stretched.

"Where am I?" She said to herself as she looked around the forest. The last 
thing she remembered was being put in a pod and sent off. Animals made noise 
around her, making her uncomfortable. She was not a social robot, so being 
around alot of beings usually made her uncomfortable.

Antagony looked down at herself and saw that she was a dark purple, with 
skin-tight armor plates attached onto her body. Her armor did a good job at 
showing off her curves. She couldn't tell exactly what she looked like since 
she didn't have a mirror, but what she saw was good. She looked up to see if 
anyone was coming.
